  "texts": [
    "To formulate our prompts, we use the \"interview-style\" prompting strategy proposed in the second study of Argyle et al. (2023).",
    "9 The control variables are given to the model in a question-answer format that imitates an interview situation: an interviewer asks questions and provides the available answers, and an interviewee chooses one of the answers (except for the age question,",
    "where they answer by a number).",
    "The socio-demographic controls are provided in the prompt, and the LLM is asked to fill in the interviewee's answer to the last question.",
    "This prompting format serves two purposes."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "To formulate our prompts, we use the \"interview-style\" prompting strategy proposed in the second study of Argyle et al. (2023)."
  ]
}